[17/10/23, 8:35:43 AM] Rakesh Gowda: Job Description

Introduction
At IBM, work is more than a job – it’s a calling: To build. To design. To code. To consult. To think along with clients and sell. To make markets. To invent. To collaborate. Not just to do something better, but to attempt things you’ve never thought possible. Are you ready to lead in this new era of technology and solve some of the world’s most challenging problems? If so, let’s talk.
“IBM Automation” invites applications for internship in Product Management at our labs in Kochi and Bangalore.

You will join a dynamic Product Management group at IBM Automation. At IBM Automation, we build best in class Automation products for different personas in an Enterprise… the Line of Business, IT and Engineering….and address a wide range of use cases like Business Process Automation, IT Observability, Application Integration, Dev Ops Automation, to name a few. You will gain significant experience, getting opportunities in performing a variety of roles in both Inbound and Outbound Product Management.

Your Role and Responsibilities
As an Intern – Product Manager, you will own outcomes. This will include:

Support seasoned Product Managers in the day-to-day and strategic management of a product.
Help define and execute product strategy.
Bring products to life through the entire product lifecycle.
Support sales and marketing initiatives to drive revenue growth.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to develop and execute a comprehensive technical roadmap.
Identify and address customer needs.
Track product performance and metrics.
Stay up-to-date on industry trends and best practices.

Required Technical and Professional Expertise

Bachelor Degree in Computer Science or related fields.
Pursuing MBA course from reputed Business School.

Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise

6 months to 1 Year exposure to one or more industry leading enterprise agile planning or development tools such as IBM Engineering Workflow Management (formally known as Rational Team Concert), Microsoft’s Github/GitLab, Aha! Portfolio Management, Atlassian’s Jira, etc.
Bachelor Degree in Computer Science or related fields.
Pursuing MBA course from reputed Business School.
1 to 2 years of Technology Industry Experience
1 to 2 years of experience as a business analyst or product manager in any industry/domain.
Understanding of product roadmaps, end-to-end lifecycles, release cadence, and support.
Experience in customer-driven usability and hypothesis-driven experimentation.
A deep passion for innovation and creating data-backed solutions.
Demonstrated ability to communicate with multiple stakeholders effectively.

[03/12/23, 8:54:01 AM] Smitha: edu okay na nodu ondsali?
[03/12/23, 8:54:19 AM] Smitha: The SSR(System Services Representative) is the primary technical interface to customers. Responsibilities include the on-site service and installation of high-volume products like printers, personal computing, and banking equipment. Additionally, an SSR may also advise customers of preventive maintenance, configuration, operation, and environmental factors which may impact product performance or impair customer’s IT operation. They may also perform activities such as systems assurance, installation planning, discontinuance, and relocation of IBM and non-IBM systems and products. Some mechanical aptitude is helpful in this position. An SSR is accountable to ensure a high level of customer satisfaction with their service delivery, technical support, and operational services in customer accounts. When critical situations occur, they manage the situation until the problem is resolved. Strong Interpersonal skills and the ability to create a connection with customers are vital in this position.
